category: ON STATES' HIGHWAY WELCOME SIGNS
category comment: (Ken: This is a road trip featuring some highway signs used in recent years.)

clue: Drivers entering from Maryland once saw the welcome signs for this state that called it "Small Wonder"

response: Delaware

clue: This farming state has welcomed visitors with "Fields of Opportunities"

response: Iowa

clue: A southern sign says, "Welcome to" this Lynyrd Skynyrd title

response: "Sweet Home Alabama"

clue: Louisiana's sign includes both "Welcome" & this French equivalent

response: Bienvenue

clue: Once on Michigan's welcome signs, this 2-word phrase that doesn't just refer to size was also on its license plates from 1983 to 2007

response: Great Lakes

